content.description: to the right of High Voltage Crack is a really nice sit down/stand up warmup. start by mantling up onto small shelf, then another mantle to top out. more than one way to do this.
prominent crack near the right end of the wall. crux is establishing the feet and the dyno that follows to a jug. from here go up and right through a flake and enjoy the highball topout.

Sit-start with your hands on the obvious jug. Move up into the sidepull seam.  Some long reaches and compression moves gets you to the rounded top.  There's a few good edges to use to pull over.  The top is a little tricky, but not too bad.
content.protection: A pad or two, and some leathery calluses -- the rock here is pretty sharp.

content.description:
Nice sunny wintertime wall to hit up with problem ranging from V0-V5 so far. Course and well featured rock with some exciting and clean topouts with flat landings. This area is a continuation of the same cliff band that you see on the side of I-95 AKA the interstate homeless camp . As of last fall all of the trees in the picture have been cut down so it looks a bit different. 

  Tons more to do around here if your hands can handle it. 

This climbing area is located in Branford, CT. No known climbing restrictions exist for this area.
